barrier_inperson: In-person instruction is currently being offered for students in grades K, 2nd, 3rd, 4th, and 5th.  A total of 69 students are participating in a hybrid program. The families of 32 students in those five grades chose not to participate in our on-campus program and decided to continue distance learning. We brought our kindergarten class back on November 9, 2020. Plans to bring in more classes were halted due to a surge in COVID-19 cases. In February, we started gradually on-boarding other classes in order to follow safety protocols. Currently, five classes/grades are operating with a hybrid schedule in order to accommodate safety protocols and families who are choosing to continue distance learning for various reasons. First grade students will be start in-person learning with a hybrid schedule on May 1st. Families were given the option to participate in our hybrid program or continue our distance learning program. Our middle school students/teachers in grades 6th, 7th and 8th operate as a team. This presents a greater challenge with in-school learning. There are no plans for the return of middle school students at this time.
